{
  "doc_id": "55684",
  "text": "For the RNA-Seq experiments, TopHat version 2.0.0 [CITATION_1] was used to align RNA-Seq reads to the reference genome (mm9) using the short read aligner Bowtie (version 2.0.0.5) [CITATION_2] . TopHat was also used to analyze the mapping results to identify splice junctions between exons. Cufflinks (version1.3.0) [CITATION_3] was used to align reads from TopHat and assemble transcripts, estimate their abundances and test for differential expression and regulation. Cuffcompare (version 1.3.0), which is part of Cufflinks was used to compare the assembled transcripts to a reference annotation. Finally, Cuffdiff (version 1.3.0) was used with settings of False Discovery Rate 0.05, Minimum Alignment Count 10, quartile normalization and bias correction to find significant changes in transcript expression, splicing and promoter use. Splicing was further visualized using Broad's Integrative Genomics Viewer (IGV) [CITATION_4] .",
